or1-last=Johnson| editor1-first=Lloyd| editor2-last=Wolff| editor2-first=Miles| title=The Encyclopedia of Minor League Baseball| edition=3rd| location=Durham, North Carolina| publisher=Baseball America| year=2007| isbn=978-1-932391-17-6}}\n\n{{1981 MLB season by team}}\n{{Texas Rangers}}\n\n[[Category:Texas Rangers seasons]]\n[[Category:1981 Major League Baseball season|Texas Rangers season]]\n[[Category:1981 in sports in Texas|Texas Rang]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2013}}\n{{Infobox MLB yearly\n| name = Texas Rangers\n| season = 1981\n| misc =\n| logo = TexasRangers 100.png\n| current league = American League\n| y1 = 1961\n| division = [[American League West|Western Division]]\n| y2 = 1972\n| Uniform logo =\n| ballpark = [[Arlington Stadium]]\n| y4 = 1972\n| city = [[Arlington, Texas]]\n| y5 = 1972\n| owners = [[Eddie Chiles]]\n| general managers = [[Eddie Robinson (baseball)|Eddie Robinson]]\n| managers = [[Don Zimmer]]\n| television = [[KXAS-TV]]<br>([[Eric Nadel]], Mel Proctor)<br>Vue-Pay<br>(Mark Holtz, Norm Hitzges)\n| radio = [[WBAP (AM)|WBAP]]<br>([[Eric Nadel]], [[Bill Merrill]], [[Mel Proctor]])\n|}}\n\n[[Image:Oakland Coliseum 1980.jpg|thumb|right|280px|The Rangers playing against the [[Oakland Athletics]] during a 1981 away game at [[Oakland\u2013Alameda County Coliseum]].]]\n\nThe '''[[Texas Rangers (baseball)|Texas Rangers]]''' '''[[1981 in baseball|1981 season]]''' involved the Rangers finishing 2nd in the [[American League West]] with a record of 57 wins and 48 losses. The season was suspended for 50 days due to the infamous 1981 players strike and the league chose as its playoff teams, the division winners from the first and second halves of the season, respectively.\n\n== Offseason ==\n* December 12, 1980: [[Richie Zisk]], [[Rick Auerbach]], [[Ken Clay]], [[Jerry Don Gleaton]], [[Brian Allard]], and Steve Finch (minors) were traded by the Rangers to the [[Seattle Mariners]] for [[Willie Horton (baseball)|Willie Horton]], [[Larry Cox (baseball catcher)|Larry Cox]], [[Rick Honeycutt]], [[Mario Mendoza]], and [[Leon Roberts]].<ref name=horton>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/h/hortowi01.shtml Willie Horton page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n* December 18, 1980: [[Bob Jones (outfielder)|Bob Jones]] was signed as a free agent by the Rangers.<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/j/jonesbo02.shtml Bob Jones page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n\n== Regular season ==\n\n=== Season standings ===\n{{1981 AL West standings}}\n\n=== Record vs. opponents ===\n{{1981 AL Record vs. opponents|team=TEX}}\n\n=== Notable transactions ===\n* April 1, 1981: Willie Horton was released by the Rangers.<ref name=horton/>\n* June 8, 1981: [[Ron Darling]] was drafted by the Rangers in the 1st round (9th pick) of the [[1981 Major League Baseball Draft]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/d/darliro01.shtml Ron Darling page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n\n=== Roster ===\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"10\" style=\"background-color: red; color: #003366; text-align: center;\" | 1981 Texas Rangers roster\n|-\n| colspan=\"10\" style=\"background-color: #003366; color: #FFFDD0; text-align: center;\" | '''Roster'''\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | '''Pitchers'''\n{{MLBplayer|46|[[Bob Babcock (baseball)|Bob Babcock]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|29|[[John Butcher (baseball)|John Butcher]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|11|[[Steve Comer]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|44|[[Danny Darwin]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|40|[[Rick Honeycutt]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|49|[[Charlie Hough]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|31|[[Ferguson Jenkins]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|38|[[John Henry Johnson (baseball)|John Henry Johnson]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|34|[[Jim Kern]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|35|[[Bob Lacey]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|32|[[Jon Matlack]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|33|[[Doc Medich]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|53|[[Mark Mercer]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|24|[[Dave Schmidt]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|12|[[Len Whitehouse]]}}\n| width=\"25px\" | \n| valign=\"top\" | '''Catchers'''\n{{MLBplayer|20|[[Larry Cox (baseball catcher)|Larry Cox]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|&nbsp;8|[[Bob Johnson (catcher)|Bob Johnson]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|10|[[Jim Sundberg]]}}\n'''Infielders'''\n{{MLBplayer|25|[[Buddy Bell]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|&nbsp;9|[[John Ellis (baseball)|John Ellis]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|14|[[Mario Mendoza]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|&nbsp;4|[[Nelson Norman]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|18|[[Pat Putnam]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|13|[[Bill Stein]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|&nbsp;3|[[Wayne Tolleson]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|30|[[Mark Wagner (shortstop)|Mark Wagner]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|&nbsp;1|[[Bump Wills]]}}\n| width=\"25px\" | \n| valign=\"top\" | '''Outfielders'''\n{{MLBplayer|21|[[Dan Duran (baseball)|Dan Duran]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|&nbsp;6|[[Johnny Grubb]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|27|[[Bobby Jones (outfielder)|Bobby Jones]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|15|[[Rick Lisi]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|16|[[Tom Poquette]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|17|[[Mickey Rivers]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|7,16|[[Leon Roberts]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|&nbsp;5|[[Billy Sample]]}}\n'''Other batters'''\n{{MLBplayer|&nbsp;0|[[Al Oliver]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|20|[[Don Werner]]}}\n| width=\"25px\" | \n| valign=\"top\" | '''Manager'''\n{{MLBplayer|23|[[Don Zimmer]]}}\n'''Coaches'''\n{{MLBplayer|41|[[Jackie Brown (baseball)|Jackie Brown]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|37|[[Tommy Helms]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|22|[[Darrell Johnson]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|47|[[Fred Koenig]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|42|[[Wayne Terwilliger]]}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== Player stats ==\n\n=== Batting ===\n\n==== Starters by position ====\n''Note: Pos = Position; G = Games played; AB = At bats; H = Hits; Avg. = Batting average; HR = Home runs; RBI = Runs batted in''\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"5%\" | Pos\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"16%\" | Player\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"9%\" | G\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"9%\" | AB\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"9%\" | H\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"9%\" | Avg.\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"9%\" | HR\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"9%\" | RBI\n|- align=\"center\"\n| SS || {{sortname|Mario|Mendoza}} || 88 || 229 || 53 || .231 || 0 || 22\n|- align=\