or1-first=Lloyd| editor2-last=Wolff| editor2-first=Miles| title=The Encyclopedia of Minor League Baseball| edition=3rd| location=Durham, North Carolina| publisher=Baseball America| year=2007| isbn=978-1-932391-17-6}}\n{{1980 MLB season by team}}\n{{Texas Rangers}}\n\n[[Category:Texas Rangers seasons]]\n[[Category:1980 Major League Baseball season|Texas Rangers season]]\n[[Category:1980 in sports in Texas|Texas Rang]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2013}}\n{{Infobox MLB yearly\n| name = Texas Rangers\n| season = 1980\n| misc =\n| logo = TexasRangers 100.png\n| current league = American League\n| y1 = 1961\n| division = [[American League West|Western Division]]\n| y2 = 1972\n| Uniform logo =\n| ballpark = [[Arlington Stadium]]\n| y4 = 1972\n| city = [[Arlington, Texas]]\n| y5 = 1972\n| owners = [[Eddie Chiles]]\n| general managers = [[Eddie Robinson (baseball)|Eddie Robinson]]\n| managers = [[Pat Corrales]]\n| television = [[KXAS-TV]]<br>([[Frank Glieber]], [[Eric Nadel]], [[Mel Proctor]])\n| radio = [[WBAP (AM)|WBAP]]<br>([[Eric Nadel]], Bill Merrill, [[Mel Proctor]])\n|}}\n\nThe '''[[Texas Rangers (baseball)|Texas Rangers]] [[1980 in baseball|1980 season]]''' involved the Rangers finishing 4th in the [[American League]] west with a record of 76 wins and 85 losses.\n\n== Offseason ==\n* November 14, 1979: [[Eric Soderholm]] was traded by the Texas Rangers to the New York Yankees for players to be named later and cash. The New York Yankees sent Amos Lewis (minors) (December 13, 1979) and Ricky Burdette (minors) (December 13, 1979) to the Texas Rangers to complete the trade.<ref>https://www.baseball-reference.com/players/s/soderer01.shtml</ref>\n* December 6, 1979: [[Doyle Alexander]], [[Larvell Blanks]] and $50,000 were traded by the Rangers to the [[Atlanta Braves]] for [[Adrian Devine]] and [[Pepe Fr\u00edas]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/a/alexado01.shtml Doyle Alexander page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n* January 4, 1980: [[Larry McCall]], [[Gary Gray (baseball)|Gary Gray]], and Mike Bucci (minors) were traded by the Rangers to the [[Cleveland Indians]] for [[David Clyde]] and [[Jim Norris]].<ref name=clyde>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/c/clydeda01.shtml David Clyde page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n* January 11, 1980: [[1980 Major League Baseball Draft]]\n**[[Billy Taylor (1990s pitcher)|Billy Taylor]] was drafted by the Rangers in the 2nd round. Player signed March 24, 1980.<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/t/taylobi04.shtml Billy Taylor page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n**[[Al Newman]] was drafted by the Rangers in the 3rd round, but did not sign.<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/n/newmaal01.shtml Al Newman page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n**[[Daryl Smith (baseball)|Daryl Smith]] was drafted by the Rangers in the 6th round.<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/s/smithda04.shtml Daryl Smith page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n* February 15, 1980: [[Willie Monta\u00f1ez]] was traded by the Rangers to the [[San Diego Padres]] for [[Gaylord Perry]], [[Tucker Ashford]] and Joe Carroll (minors).<ref name=perry>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/p/perryga01.shtml Gaylord Perry page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n* March 31, 1980: [[La Rue Washington]] and [[Chris Smith (first baseman)|Chris Smith]] were traded by the Rangers to the [[Montreal Expos]] for [[Rusty Staub]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/s/staubru01.shtml Rusty Staub page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n* March 31, 1980: David Clyde was released by the Rangers.<ref name=clyde/>\n\n== Regular season ==\n\n=== Season standings ===\n{{1980 AL West Standings}}\n\n=== Record vs. opponents ===\n{{1980 AL Record vs. opponents|team=TEX}}\n\n=== Notable transactions ===\n* June 3, 1980: [[Tom Henke]] was drafted by the Rangers in the 4th round of the [[1980 Major League Baseball Draft]] (Secondary Phase).<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/h/henketo01.shtml Tom Henke page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n* July 11, 1980: [[Charlie Hough]] was purchased by the Rangers from the [[Los Angeles Dodgers]].<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/h/houghch01.shtml Charlie Hough page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n* August 14, 1980: [[Gaylord Perry]] was traded by the Rangers to the [[New York Yankees]] for [[Ken Clay]] and a player to be named later. The Yankees completed the deal by sending Marvin Thompson (minors) to the Rangers on October 1.<ref name=perry />\n* September 13, 1980: [[Sparky Lyle]] was traded by the Rangers to the [[Philadelphia Phillies]] for a player to be named later. The Phillies completed the deal by sending [[Kevin Saucier]] to the Rangers on November 19.<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/l/lylesp01.shtml Sparky Lyle page at Baseball Reference]</ref>\n\n=== Roster ===\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"10\" style=\"background-color: red; color: #FFFDD0; text-align: center;\" | 1980 Texas Rangers roster\n|-\n| colspan=\"10\" style=\"background-color: #003366; color: #FFFDD0; text-align: center;\" | '''Roster'''\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | '''Pitchers'''\n{{MLBplayer|23|[[Brian Allard]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|46|[[Bob Babcock (baseball)|Bob Babcock]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|29|[[John Butcher (baseball)|John Butcher]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|16|[[Ken Clay]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|11|[[Steve Comer]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|44|[[Danny Darwin]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|35|[[Adrian Devine]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|24|[[Ed Figueroa]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|27|[[Jerry Don Gleaton]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|49|[[Charlie Hough]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|31|[[Ferguson Jenkins]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|38|[[John Henry Johnson (baseball)|John Henry Johnson]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|43|[[Don Kainer]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|34|[[Jim Kern]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|28|[[Dennis Lewallyn]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|28|[[Sparky Lyle]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|32|[[Jon Matlack]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|33|[[Doc Medich]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|36|[[Gaylord Perry]]}}\n{{MLBplayer|26|[[Dave Rajsich]]}}\n| width=\"25px\" | \n| valign=\"top\" | '''Catchers'''\n{{MLBplayer|10|[[Jim Sundberg]]}}\n'''Infielder